1032
01:37:33,033 --> 01:37:35,356
You made a mistake, imbecile!

1033
01:37:35,577 --> 01:37:38,290
It's your nephew. It's him.
- No it's not!

1034
01:37:38,435 --> 01:37:42,939
I sold him to the Berbers.
I took their money and spent it.

1035
01:37:43,429 --> 01:37:45,568
- Where'd you find him?
- There, in the hall.

1036
01:37:45,708 --> 01:37:48,536
He must've escaped!
I'm going crazy!

1037
01:37:49,067 --> 01:37:50,607
Let's put him with the old dame.

1038
01:38:07,595 --> 01:38:09,943
Your Majesty, my Queen,
mein Liebling.

1039
01:38:10,087 --> 01:38:13,260
You must wake up. Quick, wake up.

1040
01:38:16,365 --> 01:38:17,629
One!

1041
01:38:17,747 --> 01:38:19,052
Two!

1042
01:38:25,946 --> 01:38:29,290
- Majesty, your Majesty!
- Ich liebe dich, César.

1043
01:38:29,384 --> 01:38:32,053
Wake up. You don't understand
He wants to compromise you.

1044
01:38:32,524 --> 01:38:33,993
Küssen sie mich!

1045
01:38:34,110 --> 01:38:37,063
"Küssen sie mich"?...
Ah yes, kiss.

1046
01:38:37,291 --> 01:38:40,794
Oh, your Majesty, I'd love to,
but this is not the moment.

1047
01:38:45,913 --> 01:38:49,319
It's Blaze, I need!
Where the hell is he?

1073
01:38:49,579 --> 01:38:51,040
Ah!

1048
01:38:58,853 --> 01:39:01,032
He's there! You said he wasn't.

1049
01:39:01,157 --> 01:39:02,618
I don't understand.

1076
01:39:02,695 --> 01:39:04,053
Ah!

1050
01:39:05,297 --> 01:39:07,087
There, voilà.

1051
01:39:08,388 --> 01:39:11,357
Her, like so; 
and him, like so.

1052
01:39:24,485 --> 01:39:26,842
César, I love you.

1080
01:39:28,770 --> 01:39:29,848
Oh! Aaah!

1053
01:39:50,489 --> 01:39:51,794
Dismount!

1054
01:39:56,436 --> 01:39:58,428
César! César!

1055
01:39:58,717 --> 01:39:59,925
Come!

1056
01:40:01,564 --> 01:40:02,771
Your Majesty!

1057
01:40:08,568 --> 01:40:10,447
Search the house and bring
everybody to me.

1058
01:40:10,561 --> 01:40:11,556
Go, hurry!

1059
01:40:11,960 --> 01:40:13,181
Salluste!

1060
01:40:13,507 --> 01:40:15,384
What are you doing here?

1061
01:40:18,914 --> 01:40:20,526
Where's the Queen?

1062
01:40:22,089 --> 01:40:24,230
Did his Majesty receive
my anonymous letter?

1063
01:40:24,288 --> 01:40:25,808
Where's the Queen?

1064
01:40:27,299 --> 01:40:30,027
Upstairs, Sire. I'll show you.

1065
01:40:37,284 --> 01:40:38,396
Hurry.

1066
01:40:41,072 --> 01:40:42,185
Watch out!

1067
01:40:48,690 --> 01:40:49,792
<i>Mmf!

1068
01:40:55,833 --> 01:40:59,263
So we agree, I rendered you
a great service.

1069
01:40:59,372 --> 01:41:04,789
You repudiate the Queen and return
my titles, my money, my Fleece.

1070
01:41:06,259 --> 01:41:07,828
Here we are.

1071
01:41:29,170 --> 01:41:30,896
Sire! You, here?

1072
01:41:31,027 --> 01:41:35,949
Wake up, Juanita, my little
angel. The King is here.

1073
01:41:36,513 --> 01:41:37,634
Oh, Sire!

1074
01:41:38,233 --> 01:41:40,978
Doña Juana, have you no shame?

1075
01:41:41,158 --> 01:41:42,978
Oh no, Sire!

1076
01:41:43,653 --> 01:41:45,419
And you, César, huh?

1077
01:41:48,039 --> 01:41:50,825
- Where's the Queen?
- The Queen, here?

1078
01:41:50,993 --> 01:41:54,982
She left for Bavaria, Sire,
because of her papa is ill.

1079
01:41:56,029 --> 01:41:58,661
That's why Doña Juana and I...

1080
01:41:58,856 --> 01:42:00,692
took the opportunity.

1081
01:42:44,341 --> 01:42:45,740
Tell me, Salluste.

1082
01:42:47,294 --> 01:42:51,023
That's enough. You're in
the room of a young girl.

1083
01:42:51,466 --> 01:42:55,601
Sire, Sire!
I'm no longer a girl.

1084
01:42:55,815 --> 01:42:57,958
- Marry us.
- No, hey! Woah!

1085
01:42:58,136 --> 01:43:01,520
I mean... Let me explain, Sire.

1086
01:43:01,937 --> 01:43:03,318
Let me see if I can.

1087
01:43:03,655 --> 01:43:07,695
There's nobody else. We searched
everything. Only found these two.

1088
01:43:09,486 --> 01:43:11,630
Who are these two men?
Salluste!

1089
01:43:12,603 --> 01:43:14,091
Where is he?

1090
01:43:18,435 --> 01:43:19,648
Giddy up.

1091
01:43:27,621 --> 01:43:28,862
César.

1092
01:43:29,784 --> 01:43:31,472
Küssen Sie mich!

1093
01:43:32,294 --> 01:43:33,521
What did she say?

1094
01:43:33,637 --> 01:43:35,427
Kiss her, you fool.

1095
01:43:44,963 --> 01:43:47,618
Salluste!
Where are you going?

1096
01:43:47,757 --> 01:43:49,524
Nowhere, Sire.

1097
01:43:50,850 --> 01:43:52,911
I was looking for your Majesty.

1098
01:43:53,460 --> 01:43:54,919
So, Salluste...

1099
01:43:57,511 --> 01:43:59,075
am I a cuckold?

1100
01:44:16,957 --> 01:44:18,230
Wait!

1101
01:44:19,827 --> 01:44:21,230
Wait!

1102
01:44:32,870 --> 01:44:34,238
Yalla!

1103
01:44:39,838 --> 01:44:41,502
Look who's coming.

1104
01:44:41,783 --> 01:44:43,494
Look who's there.

1105
01:44:43,956 --> 01:44:45,353
The Grandees!

1106
01:44:57,823 --> 01:44:58,987
Yalla!

1107
01:45:00,294 --> 01:45:04,251
I have the ritziest penal colony
in all of Sahara.

1108
01:45:19,596 --> 01:45:21,885
Anyway, we're not going
to rot here.

1109
01:45:21,904 --> 01:45:24,193
I have a little plan to escape.

1110
01:45:24,380 --> 01:45:25,706
We go back to Madrid.

1111
01:45:25,860 --> 01:45:27,352
We conspire together.

1112
01:45:27,710 --> 01:45:29,622
The King repudiates the Queen.

1113
01:45:29,747 --> 01:45:31,684
The old dame marries the parrot.

1114
01:45:31,818 --> 01:45:33,391
César becomes King.

1115
01:45:33,551 --> 01:45:36,029
I marry him and voilà, I'm the Queen!

1116
01:45:37,099 --> 01:45:42,005
Listen, Salluste, don't you notice your
head swelling enormously sometimes?

1117
01:45:42,250 --> 01:45:43,630
Know what I mean?

1118
01:45:44,735 --> 01:45:47,615
What are you doing here
then, my dear César?

1119
01:45:47,847 --> 01:45:50,286
His name is not César.
It's Blaze.

1120
01:45:51,485 --> 01:45:53,427
The King said to me:
"You have a choice.

1121
01:45:54,115 --> 01:45:56,808
Either you marry Doña Juana,
or it's the Berbers for you.

1122
01:45:56,915 --> 01:45:58,105
And?

1123
01:45:58,222 --> 01:46:00,162
And it's the Berbers.

1124
01:46:02,441 --> 01:46:03,894
Yoohoo!

1125
01:46:04,391 --> 01:46:05,801
César!

1126
01:46:05,891 --> 01:46:06,901
Oh no!

1127
01:46:07,609 --> 01:46:08,354
The old dame!

1128
01:46:08,609 --> 01:46:10,848
César! César!

1129
01:46:11,109 --> 01:46:13,893
I'm here! It's me!

1130
01:46:14,150 --> 01:46:15,477
Oh no!

1131
01:46:15,734 --> 01:46:18,269
Oh no, help!

1132
01:46:27,048 --> 01:46:28,043
Help!

1133
01:46:28,136 --> 01:46:31,677
César, wait for me,
my love.

1134
01:46:34,200 --> 01:46:39,690
